'''Mohamed "Moi" Elyounoussi''' (born 4 August 1994) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] or [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for English club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton.]] He represents [[Norway national football team|Norway]] at senior international level.
== Early life == {{Expand section|date=July 2018}} Elyounoussi was born in [[Al Hoceima]], Morocco. He grew up in [[Sarpsborg]], [[Norway]], where he also started his football career.
==Club career== ===Sarpsborg 08=== He made his debut in [[Tippeligaen]] when he came on as a [[Substitute (association football)|sub]] in [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]]'s match against [[Odd Grenland]] on 8 May 2011.
===Molde=== On 15 March 2014, Elyounoussi moved to fellow [[Tippeligaen]] side [[Molde FK]].<ref name="Moi">{{cite news|url=http://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/selger-elyounoussi-til-tippeligarival/5177734.html|language=Norwegian|title=Selger Elyounoussi til tippeligarival|work=Nettavisen|date=15 March 2014|accessdate=14 April 2014}}</ref> During his first season with Molde FK he played in every league match and was the club's top scorer with 13 goals.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.moldefk.no/news/article/tsnc5v4yctrh18bdvqk4zfzik/title/toppscoreren|language=Norwegian|title=Toppscorern|work=Molde FK|date=9 December 2014|accessdate=20 January 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150122022636/http://www.moldefk.no/news/article/tsnc5v4yctrh18bdvqk4zfzik/title/toppscoreren|archivedate=22 January 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> With the club, Elyounoussi won both Tippeligaen and the [[Norwegian Football Cup|Norwegian Cup]] in his first season, which meant that Molde won the double for the first time in the club's history. He scored four goals in the [[2014 Norwegian Football Cup|2014 Norwegian Cup]], of which one was sored in the [[2014 Norwegian Football Cup Final|final]] against [[Odds BK|Odd]]. Elyounoussi scored a total of 17 goals in all competitions in the 2014 season and became Molde's top goalscorer.
In 2015, Elyounoussi scored three goals in the [[2015–16 UEFA Europa League]], all in the group stage. He scored twice against [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000658/match=2016971/index.html |title=Molde 3-1 Celtic Match Report |website=www.uefa.com |publisher=[[UEFA]] |accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000658/match=2016995/index.html?iv=true |title=Celtic 1-2 Molde Match Report |website=www.uefa.com |publisher=[[UEFA]] |accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref> and once against [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000658/match=2016923/index.html |title=Fenerbache 1-3 Molde Match Report |website=www.uefa.com |publisher=[[UEFA]] |accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref> and helped the team advance to the Round of 16 where they lost 1–3 on aggregate against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].
===Basel=== On 6 July 2016, Elyounoussi moved to [[Swiss Super League]] side [[FC Basel]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mohamed Elyounoussi wechselt zum FCB|url=http://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2016/07/06/Mohamed-Elyounoussi-wechselt-zum-FCB|website=fcb.ch|publisher=FC Basel|accessdate=6 July 2016|date=6 July 2016|language=German}}</ref> He made his first team league debut on 24 July in the 3–0 home win against [[FC Sion|Sion]].<ref name="fcb 2016-07-24">{{cite web | first = Caspar | last = Marti | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = 2016 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2016/07/24/FCB-Sion| title = 3:0 gegen Sion – Der FCB war beim Auftact parat | format = | work = | publisher = FC Basel 1893 | accessdate = 2016-07-24}}</ref> He scored his first goal for his new club just one week later on 31 July during the away game against [[FC Vaduz|Vaduz]]. It was the third Basler goal of the game and they won 5–1.<ref name="fcb 2016-07-31">{{cite web | first = Caspar | last = Marti | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = 2016 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2016/07/31/Vaduz-FCB | title = Klarer Sieg beim FC Vaduz | format = | work = | publisher = FC Basel 1893 | accessdate = 2016-07-31}}</ref> Elyounoussi scored a hat trick for Basel on 4 February 2017 during the home game against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]]. These were the first three goals and were scored during the first 36 minutes of the game that Basel won 4–0.<ref name="fcb 2017-02-04">{{cite web | first = Caspar | last = Marti | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = 2017 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2017/02/04/FCB-Lugano | title = Elyounoussi hattrick beim 4:0 gegen Lugano| format = | work = | publisher = FC Basel 1893 | accessdate = 2017-02-04}}</ref> Under trainer [[Urs Fischer (footballer)|Urs Fischer]], Elyounoussi won the [[Swiss Super League]] championship at the end of the [[2016–17 Swiss Super League|2016–17 season]]. For the club this was the eighth title in a row and their 20th championship title in total.<ref name="fcb 2017-06-02">{{cite web | first = Casper | last = Marti | authorlink = | coauthors = | year = 2017 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/de-CH/News/2017/06/02/Der-Saisonabschluss-im-Zeitraffer | title = Der Saisonabschluss im Zeitraffer | format = | work = | publisher = FC Basel 1893 | accessdate = 2017-06-02}}</ref> They also won the [[Swiss Cup]] for the twelfth time, which meant they had won the double for the sixth time in the club's history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Swiss football: FC Basel wins 3-0 over Sion in Geneva; police extra vigilant after game|url=https://allaboutgeneva.com/2017/05/25/swiss-football-fc-basel-wins-3-0-over-sion-in-geneva-police-extra-vigilant-after-game|publisher=allaboutgeneva.com|date=25 May 2017}}</ref>
===Southampton=== On 29 June 2018, Elyounoussi was signed by [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] for a reported fee of £16 million,<ref>{{cite web |title=Mohamed Elyounoussi signs for Southampton from Basel for reported £16m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44658749 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=29 June 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref> signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Saints sign Elyounoussi |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2018-06-29/announcement-southampton-mohamed-elyounoussi-fc-basel-transfer |publisher=Southampton FC |accessdate=29 June 2018 |date=29 June 2018}}</ref>
==International career== In June 2011, Elyounoussi was called up for the [[Norway national under-17 football team|Norway U-17]] team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sa.no/sport/sarpsborg08/article5655243.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Mohamed Elyounoussi på G17-landslaget |work=sa.no |publisher=[[Sarpsborg Arbeiderblad]] |date=28 June 2011 |accessdate=13 February 2012}}</ref>
In November 2013, he was called up to the senior [[Norway national football team|Norwegian national team]] for their January 2014 international matches in [[Abu Dhabi]].<ref>{{cite web|title=HERRELANDSLAGETS TROPP TIL JANUAR-KAMPER|url=https://www.fotball.no/Landslag_og_toppfotball/Landslag/A-menn/2013/Herrelandslagets-tropp-til-januar-kamper/|publisher=fotball.no|accessdate=14 April 2014|language=Norwegian|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131206123859/http://www.fotball.no/Landslag_og_toppfotball/Landslag/A-menn/2013/Herrelandslagets-tropp-til-januar-kamper/|archivedate=6 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He made his debut there against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] on 18 January 2014, replacing [[Erik Huseklepp]] in the 33rd minute of a 3&ndash;0 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|title=18.01.2014 Norway v Poland|url=http://eu-football.info/_match.php?id=674|publisher=eu-football.info|accessdate=14 April 2014}}</ref> He scored his first goal for [[Norway national football team|Norway]] on 13 June 2017 against [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]]. He scored his first [[hat-trick]] for Norway on 5 October 2017 against [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]].
