==Personal life== Elyounoussi is of [[Moroccans|Moroccan]] descent, his family immigrated to Norway when he was a child. He was thus eligible to play for the [[Moroccan national football team]] but opted for [[Norway national football team|Norway]]. He is the cousin of [[Tarik Elyounoussi]], who is also a Norwegian international footballer who plays for AIK in Sweden.
Elyounoussi’s father owns a [[pizza parlor]] in Norway.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Heneage|first1=Kristan|title=Mohamed Elyounoussi: The pizza-loving forward Leicester are eyeing as Mahrez's replacement|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/mohamed-elyounoussi-pizza-loving-forward-leicester-are-eyeing-mahrezs-replacement|website=FourFourTwo|accessdate=17 June 2016|date=24 March 2016}}</ref>
