{{Infobox football biography | name = Callum Slattery | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Callum Slattery<ref>{{cite news|title=Premier League clubs publish retained lists|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/408901|language=en}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1999|2|8|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Kidlington]], England | height = {{height|m=1.75}} | position = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] | clubnumber = 55 | youthyears1 = –2008 | youthclubs1 = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] | youthyears2= 2008–2017 | youthclubs2= [[Southampton F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Southampton]] | years1 = 2017– | clubs1 = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] | caps1 = 3 | goals1 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2014–2015 |nationalteam1 = [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] |nationalcaps1 = 5 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2014–2015 |nationalteam2 = [[England national under-16 football team|England U16]] |nationalcaps2 = 4 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |nationalyears3 = 2017 |nationalteam3 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] |nationalcaps3 = 3 |nationalgoals3 = 0 | club-update = 08:56, 3 February 2019 (UTC) | ntupdate = 17:16, 5 January 2019 (UTC) }}
'''Callum Slattery''' (born 8 February 1999) is an English [[association Football|footballer]] who plays for [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] as a midfielder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/callum-slattery/453420/|title=England - C. Slattery - Profile with news, career statistics and history |website=us.soccerway.com}}</ref>
==Professional career== In July 2017, Slattery signed a 3-year professional contract with the Saints.<ref>{{cite web |title=Slattery looking to kick on |url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-07-08/callum-slattery-on-southampton-ambitions |publisher=Southampton FC |accessdate=5 January 2019 |date=8 July 2017}}</ref> Slattery was named in the starting eleven of the first team on 5 January 2019 in the [[FA Cup]] third round against [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] at [[Pride Park]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Derby 2–2 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46706909 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=5 January 2019 |date=5 January 2019}}</ref>
==International career== Slattery was part of the [[England national under-20 football team|England]] team that won the [[2017 Toulon Tournament]]. He scored the fourth penalty in the shoot-out in the final against [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Saints youngster Callum Slattery helps England to tournament glory |url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15342163.saints-youngster-helps-england-to-tournament-glory/ |accessdate=5 January 2019 |work=Daily Echo |date=12 June 2017 |location=Southampton}}</ref>
